╭─ Assistant [MainThread@1654807] ──────────────────────────────────────────────╮
│ Proposed fix summary:                                                         │
│ - Skip applying MinBWs narrowing to gather nodes and ensure gather element    │
│ type is widened to accommodate any getValueType widths of gathered scalars.   │
│ This prevents lossy truncation during build-vector creation that can change   │
│ compare semantics.                                                            │
│                                                                               │
│ Patch:                                                                        │
│ - File: llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp                       │
│ - Changes:                                                                    │
│   - In vectorizeTree, avoid MinBWs narrowing when E->isGather().              │
│   - For gathers of integer scalars, set ScalarTy to the maximum bitwidth seen │
│ from getValueType for each gathered scalar before creating the build vector.  │
│                                                                               │
│ Rationale:                                                                    │
│ - The miscompile occurs because the SLP vectorizer reduces the element width  │
│ for a gather to i16, then performs an i16 signed compare. In the original     │
│ scalar code, operands are i32, so narrowing changes the comparison result. By │
│ ensuring gathers use a sufficiently wide element type and skipping MinBWs for │
│ gathers, we avoid truncation that leads to wrong icmp results.                │
│                                                                               │
│ Note:                                                                         │
│ - There are still complex cases where compare operands are formed from        │
│ different trees and the gathered values are not directly the same as the      │
│ compare operands. The minimal safe change avoids the immediate truncation bug │
│ without broadly impacting MinBWs benefits elsewhere. Further refinements      │
│ could be added to upcast ICmp operands based on original scalar widths if     │
